What about this:

```
    "thumbnails": [
        {
            "ratio": "16by9",
            "file": "../thumbs/16by9.png"
        }, {
            "ratio": "9by16",
            "file": "../thumbs/9by16.png"
        }, {
            "ratio": "1by1",
            "file": "../thumbs/1by1.png"
        } 
    ]
```

We could define a bunch of predefined aspect ratios. I guess there are less than actual resolutions. The images could be as big as the renderer the template runs on (1920x1080 etc.) or as small as the author see fit. The whole thing ("thumbnails" object) could be optional. Also the ratio could be optional, but then it would not make much sense to have more than one entry in the array.

I think we should include the `CEF`-version in the version descriptor, to allow for potential other rendering engines in the future.
Something like this, perhaps?
```json
{
    "renderRequirements": [
        {
            "engine": {
                "cefVersion": { "min": 139 }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

What about:
```
{
    "renderRequirements": [
        {
            "engine": {
                "type": "CEF",
                "version": { "min": 139 }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```
Would allow other engines, like Gecko etc.

The original proposal would do so as well, when used like so:
```json
{
    "renderRequirements": [
        {
            "engine": {
                "cefVersion": { "min": 139 },
                "geckoVersion": { "min": 106 }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```
That said, I would still prefer @didikunz 's version, since it is a bit more verbose.

Or a combination of both:

```
{
    "renderRequirements": [
        {
            "engine": [
				{
					"type": "CEF",
					"minVersion": 139
				},
				{
					"type": "Gecko",
					"minVersion": 106
				}
			]
        }
}
```

The version could always be a minimal version, so that could be shorthanded, or could left as is for compatibility with other numeric values, that have a range etc. In this way different engines could be mention, without having fixed assomptions on types. So it could also be vendor specific types.

What we discussed during the meeting on 2025-10-29:

```
{
    "renderRequirements": [
        {
            "engine": [
				{
					"type": "CEF",
					"version": { "min": 139 }
				},
				{
					"type": "Gecko",
					"version": { "min": 106 }
				}
			]
        }
}
```

