## Proposal:

Add a `useInName?: boolean` property to the manifest schema properties. When `useInName = true`, this indicates that the value of the property should be included when labelling a graphics in a GUI.

## Motivation:

When working on implementing OGraf support into [Sofie TV Automation](https://sofie-automation.github.io/), I found that this would have been nice to have, in order to display meaningful labels to the user (and omit not-so-useful data).

### Example:

```json
{
    "$schema": "https://ograf.ebu.io/v1/specification/json-schemas/graphics/schema.json",
    "id": "title",
    "name": "Title screen",
    "main": "title.js",
    "schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
            "mainText": {
                "type": "string",
                "title": "Main Title text",
                "useInName": true
            },
            "titleColor": {
                "type": "string",
                "default": "#d32f2f"
            },
            "titlePosition": {
                "type": "string"
            },
        }
    }
}
```

In this example, `mainText` would be useful to display in a gui (eg "Title screen: Johan Nyman"), whereas the color and position is not.

(The suggestions below are intended to spark discussion, perhaps we can come up with something even better?)

## Background

There are some graphics that take position data as input. One example is this one from the olympics:

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93cae12f-034f-4755-947c-83e4caba6f22)


## Relative position

Below are suggestions for how relative positions could be defined.
I include a `typicalValue`, with the intention that it is used to scale the input, so that "one human interaction" (like "one scroll", "one drag operation" or "one swipe") typically result in sent values with a sum in this magnitude.

```json
{
  "type": "number",
  "gddType": "relative-position-1d",
  "gddOptions": {
    "typicalValue": 100 // [Optional, number] A typical value during one interaction (An interaction can be a drag, or a scroll, etc).
  }
}
```
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "gddType": "relative-position-2d",
  "gddOptions": {
    "typicalValueX": 100, // [Optional, number] A typical value during one interaction (An interaction can be a drag, or a scroll, etc).
    "typicalValueY": 100 // [Optional, number] A typical value during one interaction (An interaction can be a drag, or a scroll, etc).
  },
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
    }
  }
}
```
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "gddType": "relative-position-3d",
  "gddOptions": {
    "typicalValueX": 100, // [Optional, number] A typical value during one interaction (An interaction can be a drag, or a scroll, etc).
    "typicalValueY": 100, // [Optional, number] A typical value during one interaction (An interaction can be a drag, or a scroll, etc).
    "typicalValueZ": 100 // [Optional, number] A typical value during one interaction (An interaction can be a drag, or a scroll, etc).
  },
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
    },
    "z": {
      "type": "number",
    }
  }
}
```

## Absolute position

Below are suggestions for how absolute positions could be defined.
The min/max values should be used by a GUI to define the values sent.


```json
{
  "type": "number",
  "gddType": "absolute-position-1d",
  "gddOptions": {},
  "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
  "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
  "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
  "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
}
```

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "gddType": "absolute-position-2d",
  "gddOptions": {},
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    }
  }
}
```

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "gddType": "absolute-position-3d",
  "gddOptions": {},
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    },
    "z": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    }
  }
}
```

### Absolute positions - variants

#### GPS position

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "gddType": "absolute-position-2d/gps", // X and Y are longitude and latitude, respectively.
  "gddOptions": {},
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    }
  }
}
```

#### Position on screen

(This would be used for the example screenshot above)

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "gddType": "absolute-position-2d/screen", // X and Y are positions on a screen with (0,0) being the top-left corner of the screen.
  "gddOptions": {},
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
      "maximum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMaximum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "minimum": number,          // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
      "exclusiveMinimum": number, // [Optional] See JSON-schema definition
    }
  }
}
```

